                     <physloc label="Identifier:">
								MS Add. 439, <title render="doublequote" linktype="simple">Poems</title> section, 
								109-112
							</physloc>
                     <physloc label="Building:">The Archives</physloc>
                     <repository>YMAR</repository>
                     <note>
                        <p>MS catalogued by <persname normal="Huber, Alexander">Alexander 
									Huber</persname> in The Archives, York Minster Library &amp; Archives, on <date normal="20070327" era="ce" calendar="gregorian">27/03/2007</date>.</p>
                     </note>
                  </did>
                  <scopecontent>
                     <p>Transcript in an unidentified neat and legible hand, entitled <title render="doublequote" linktype="simple">Epitaph on M<emph render="super">rs</emph>. Clarke</title>
								(p. 109) (<title render="doublequote" linktype="simple">Epitaph. I.</title> [p. 111]). The
								poem, which is annotated "This Lady, the Wife of D<emph render="super">r</emph>. Clarke, Physician at Epsom, died April, 27,
								1757; and is buried in the Church of Beckenham, Kent" on the title
								page, is	part of a	section called <title render="doublequote" linktype="simple">Poems</title>, which is 
								separately paginated and has its own table of contents (p. 129), in a
								volume entitled <title render="italic" linktype="simple">Gray's Poems</title>. The book
								carries the bookplate of <persname normal="Gray, Thomas, 1716-1771" source="lcnaf">Gray</persname>'s friend and biographer <extref href="http://www.thomasgray.org/resources/glnames.shtml#Mason, William, 1724-1797"
                                show="replace"
                                linktype="simple">
                           <persname normal="Mason, William, 1724-1797">William
											Mason</persname>
                        </extref>.
							</p>
                  </scopecontent>
